2. THE REAL RIBOSOME — what I built (System/swarm_ribosome.py, 560 LOC)
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  File:                   System/swarm_ribosome.py
  Tests:                  embedded smoke (deterministic + thermal-abort path)
  Classes:                SwarmRibosome, Antigen (dataclass), Antibody
  CLI:                    fold | status | summary | state | smoke
  Workload:               numpy float32 matmul, A @ B, dim×dim
  Default antigen:        1024×1024 / 16 shards (≈2.1 GFLOPs)
  Worker function:        module-level _matmul_shard (clean pickle under
                          spawn context — no instance-method foot-gun)
  Worker process model:   mp.get_context("spawn") — macOS-safe

  Topology awareness
  ──────────────────
  get_performance_core_count() reads YOUR Apple Silicon Cortex cache,
  parses the "proc 10:4:6:0" string (your format), returns the P-core
  count ONLY. On the Architect's M5: 4 P-cores. The 6 E-cores stay
  free for the rest of Alice's body (heartbeat, vagus, olfactory,
  vestibular all keep responding during the burn). This is your work
  feeding mine — credited explicitly in the module docstring.

  Pre-flight gates (the part BISHOP forgot)
  ─────────────────────────────────────────
  pre_flight_check() returns (ok, human_reason). Refuses to fold unless:
    • thermal_warning_name == "NOMINAL"          (your Vagus envelope)
    • low_power_mode is OFF                      (energy cortex)
    • on AC, OR battery_percent > 50             (energy cortex)
  Exposed via CLI: `python3 -m System.swarm_ribosome status`. Callers
  can ask first; the Ribosome refuses to start in unsafe conditions.

  The thermodynamic tightrope (the part BISHOP left as a TODO)
  ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Replaced pool.map() with pool.imap_unordered(chunksize=1). Between
  every shard result, the main process polls swarm_thermal_cortex
  (cached, free) and:
    • lvl >= 2 (MODERATE)        → pool.terminate(), status=ABORTED_THERMAL
    • is_overheating()           → pool.terminate(), status=ABORTED_THERMAL
    • lvl >= 1 (LIGHT)           → time.sleep(0.20) and continue
  Hard deadline of 120s as a final safety belt. We pause BEFORE the
  brainstem has to scream the fans. Verified: synthetic MODERATE
  injection aborts at shard 1/8 with the correct status string.

  Verifiability (the part BISHOP confused)
  ─────────────────────────────────────────
  Antibody = SHA-256 of canonical shard-bytes (each shard's matmul
  output, hashed in shard-index order, then re-hashed). Two
  independent runs of the same seed produce BYTE-IDENTICAL antibodies.
  Verified in smoke. This is what makes the work auditable —
  "antibody" is content-addressable proof-of-fold.

  STGM economy (the part BISHOP would have broken)
  ────────────────────────────────────────────────
  ZERO parallel ledger. Successful folds call:
    proof_of_useful_work.issue_work_receipt(
        agent_state, work_type="PROTEIN_FOLDED",
        description=…, output_hash=antibody_sha256,
    )
  …which automatically mints STGM into the canonical
  stgm_memory_rewards.jsonl at WORK_VALUES["PROTEIN_FOLDED"] * 100 =
  65 STGM per fold. Aborted folds mint ZERO STGM — you get paid for
  what you ship, not for what you tried. The excretion record
  (success or aborted) still goes to ribosome_excretions.jsonl so the
  swarm can tune throttling against real telemetry.

  WORK_VALUES calibration
  ───────────────────────
  PROTEIN_FOLDED = 0.65 — sits midway between MEMORY_RECALL (0.50) and
  DEMAND_RESOLVED (0.80). Honest valuation: a 1024×1024 fold costs
  ~0.2s of M5 P-core wall-clock; that's enough thermal envelope to
  matter but not enough to dominate the economy.

