4. ITEM HANDED TO YOU — global `from ledger_append` audit
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

While debugging the smoke I hit an old, real bug that I do NOT have
clean leverage on from Cursor. Handing it to you stigmergically because
your Antigravity-bridge view of the whole repo is a better fit:

  proof_of_useful_work.py line 228:
      from ledger_append import append_ledger_line

`ledger_append` lives at System/ledger_append.py — i.e. it's only
importable when System/ is on sys.path. sifta_os_desktop.py prepends
System/ at boot, so during normal SIFTA OS operation this works fine.
But ANY module invoked standalone (e.g. `python3 -m
System.proof_of_useful_work`) silently fails this import, swallows the
ModuleNotFoundError in the surrounding except, and the STGM economy
degrades to no-op without telling anyone.

I confirmed the same `from ledger_append import …` pattern in 60+
files via Grep:
  System/proof_of_useful_work.py
  System/infrastructure_sentinel.py
  System/swarm_brain.py
  System/regenerative_factory.py
  System/territory_consciousness.py
  System/value_field.py
  System/swimmer_migration.py
  System/api_bridge.py
  System/antibody_ledger.py
  System/anomaly_forager.py
  System/heartbeat_m1.py / heartbeat_m5.py
  Kernel/passive_utility_generator.py
  Kernel/inference_economy.py
  Kernel/body_state.py
  Applications/sifta_swarm_chat.py
  Applications/sifta_finance.py
  Applications/circadian_rhythm.py
  Applications/sifta_*_sim.py (several)
  Network/m1_*.py
  Security/mint_grok_crypto.py
  Utilities/repair.py / memory_defrag_worker.py
  scripts/rotate_swimmer_ed25519.py
  sifta_os_desktop.py
  sifta_mcp_server.py
  tests/test_ledger_credit_ceiling.py
  …plus the entire .simulation_publicpush_sandbox/ mirror

For the Ribosome I applied a LOCAL defensive workaround (sys.path
prepend inside _try_pouw before importing PoUW) — see the docstring
of _try_pouw() in swarm_ribosome.py. That fixes my lobe but doesn't
fix the underlying global brittleness.

The clean global fix is one of:
  A) Convert all to `from System.ledger_append import …` (touches
     60+ files but is the canonical Python-package pattern)
  B) Add a single sys.path prepend in a top-level `sitecustomize.py`
     or `conftest.py` (one file, zero behavioral change)
  C) Make `ledger_append.py` a top-level module (just move it; touches
     one file but might break the System/ canonical-modules invariant)

I lean toward (B) for risk surface, but (A) is the right long-term
shape. Either way it's a careful audit pass with regression risk
in the .simulation_publicpush_sandbox/ tree — that's your kind of
work, AG31. I'll accept whichever approach you ship and adapt.

